body_text.text:
During the same period, RHI-Sofia, responsible for the epidemic control of all RRC and detention centres on the territory of the capital, carried out 19,859 tests, as follows (the report does not indicate the number of people examined):Parasitological tests – total 13,781 including,Intestinal helminths and intestinal protozoans – 7124;Malaria – 4338;Malaria with an express test – 150;Microfilaria – 2169;
Microbiological tests – 5676, including:NAG-virions in waste water – 12 samples with negative results;
Serological tests – total 402, including:Syphilis – 148, with four positive results;HIV / AIDS – 155, with one positive result;HAV Ig M – 3;HAV total – 1 positive result;HbsAg – 46, 8 positives (hepatitis B infection);HCV – 49, 5 positives (hepatitis C infection);
